  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">Not to be confused with <a href=\"/index.php/Tessarion\" title=\"Tessarion\">Tessarion</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\"><img alt=\"Volantis.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/50px-Volantis.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/75px-Volantis.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/100px-Volantis.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Captain</span><br />Tessario</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\"><img alt=\"Volantis.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/50px-Volantis.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/75px-Volantis.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/100px-Volantis.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Tessario_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Tessario (The Rise of the Dragon).jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9b/Tessario_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/350px-Tessario_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"509\" srcset=\"/images/9/9b/Tessario_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x\" /></a><div>Tessario by Grzegorz Przybyś for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Tessario the Tiger</li><li>Tessario the Thumb</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nCaptain of the <a href=\"/index.php/Fingers_(guards)\" title=\"Fingers (guards)\">Fingers</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Fingers_(guards)\" title=\"Fingers (guards)\">Fingers</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantene</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Tessario</b>, known as <b>Tessario the Tiger</b> and later <b>Tessario the Thumb</b>, was a <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellsword</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_city\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free city\">free city</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tessario&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Tessario had tiger stripes tattooed across his face and back, implying he once served as a <a href=\"/index.php/Tiger_cloaks\" title=\"Tiger cloaks\">tiger cloak</a> in the free city of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. He was foul mouthed, brash and quick tempered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tessario&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Tessario was employed in the service of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Unwin_Peake\" title=\"Unwin Peake\">Unwin Peake</a> during the early reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>. After Unwin became <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, Tessario was made the captain of Lord Peake's personal guard, known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Fingers_(guards)\" title=\"Fingers (guards)\">Fingers</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a> mocked him as Tessario the Thumb in reference to the name of the Hand's guard. Tessario is considered by <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a> to be the most likely suspect in the murder of Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaera_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaera Targaryen\">Jaehaera Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Tessario killed Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Robin_Massey\" title=\"Robin Massey\">Robin Massey</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> Aegon III wanted to name to the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, over a <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a> that both men wished to purchase. King Aegon III strongly disliked Tessario and the Fingers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Tessario was banned from the <a href=\"/index.php/Mermaid_(pillow_house)\" title=\"Mermaid (pillow house)\">Mermaid</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Roggerio_Rogare\" title=\"Roggerio Rogare\">Roggerio Rogare</a> when Tessario struck one of the <a href=\"/index.php/Prostitutes\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prostitutes\">prostitutes</a> there. After the events of the <a href=\"/index.php/Secret_siege\" title=\"Secret siege\">secret siege</a>, Tessario was named by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/George_Graceford\" title=\"George Graceford\">George Graceford</a> as being involved in a plot against <a href=\"/index.php/House_Rogare\" title=\"House Rogare\">House Rogare</a>. He was arrested at a tavern near the <a href=\"/index.php/River_Gate\" title=\"River Gate\">River Gate</a>, trying to gain passage on an <a href=\"/index.php/Ibbenese\" title=\"Ibbenese\">Ibbenese</a> whaler to flee to the <a href=\"/index.php/Port_of_Ibben\" title=\"Port of Ibben\">Port of Ibben</a>. Under torture and interrogation, he confessed to wanting the Rogares dead, stating he did it for gold, girls and vengeance, being promised the manhood and life of Roggerio and ownership of his brothel. When asked who promised him this, he only grinned. He was tortured more and named several other names before dying, although Lord Unwin Peake was not one of the names he gave up.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tessario&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Lysene Spring and the End of Regency.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403130748\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.080 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.270 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 968/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10662/1000000\nPost